NGINX load balancer is defaulted to round robin.
Currently supports caching using pymemcache, caching could also be done using the google.appengine 
(https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/cloud-gae-python-migrate-12-memcache#4)
(default - http://127.0.0.1/)

Currently using uWSGI, check refs.

ref: 
    - https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/load-balancing-flask-application-using-nginx-and-docker/
    - https://uwsgi-docs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/WSGIquickstart.html


links:
    - https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18071652/handling-http-requests-with-c-in-nginx
    - http://chriswu.me/blog/writing-hello-world-in-fcgi-with-c-plus-plus/